  "body": "**Describe the bug**\r\n\r\nreplica-healthcheck 1.0.1 started from official docker image fails with\r\n\r\n```\r\nreplica-healthcheck_1   | npm ERR! A complete log of this run can be found in:\r\nreplica-healthcheck_1   | npm ERR!     /root/.npm/_logs/2022-03-22T14_08_43_686Z-debug.log\r\nreplica-healthcheck_1   | npm ERR! code ENOENT\r\nreplica-healthcheck_1   | npm ERR! syscall open\r\nreplica-healthcheck_1   | npm ERR! path /opts/optimism/packages/replica-healthcheck/package.json\r\nreplica-healthcheck_1   | npm ERR! errno -2\r\nreplica-healthcheck_1   | npm ERR! enoent ENOENT: no such file or directory, open '/opts/optimism/packages/replica-healthcheck/package.json'\r\nreplica-healthcheck_1   | npm ERR! enoent This is related to npm not being able to find a file.\r\nreplica-healthcheck_1   | npm ERR! enoent\r\n```\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\n\r\nCan an enhancement request be added? replica-healthcheck docker images have been unhealthy for a while. How about adding CI/CD that specifically tests the docker build pipeline for it?\r\n",
